<br>
The only real thing I see these doing from within a group (or raid for that matter) is making it easier for group members to leave.  With a mage AND a wizard in a group, we can now summon new people, and get rid of old people, without ANY interruption to the group environment.  It does nothing to improve the fight itself, but hey, this is Verant we are talking about.  Yet another feeble attempt at creativity.<br>
<br>
And before they say, &quot;You all are never satisfied...&quot;  show us one SINGLE SOLITARY IDEA that actually presents a LAUDIBLE level of balance to the class.<br>
<br>
And actually, I will say that the resist rate for Atol's is a pretty cheap (yet &quot;ok&quot;) addition.  Very useful, but more in the soloing realm where the snare HAS to hit on the first try.  In a group, there is usually no emergiency if you have to cast it two or three times.  But if you miss a snare at Raptor island, it is MUCH more interesting to recover from.  So indirectly, they just contradicted themselves.  They wouldn't give us manaregen because they thought it would promote increased soloing.  But this snare change is a MAJOR improvement in the solo side of fighting.  Quadding to be specific.  Just my opinion of course.<br>
<br>
W.F. <br>
